etball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The top two from each group along with the two best third-placed teams will progress to the next round.\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 824, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Then a draw will take place to determine the pairings of the quarterfinals.\", \"from\": 825, \"to\": 900, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The winners of the quarterfinals will progress to the semifinals.\", \"from\": 902, \"to\": 967, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The winners of the semifinals meet in the gold medal match while the losers play in the bronze medal match.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 1075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans' dominant status in Olympic men's basketball makes them the heavy favourites in Paris.\", \"from\": 1079, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1079, \"end\": 1092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3445939635875628e-15, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}, {\"begin\": 1173, \"end\": 1178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999990609467, \"rank\": 9.391310683520743e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA have won a record 16 gold medals out of a possible 20 - including a first-place finish in the last four Summer Games.\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1181, \"end\": 1189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.728184769295006e-18, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They can expect a challenge from their northern neighbours, Canada, who boast the star-studded NBA guard tandem of Shai Gilgeous-Alexander and Jamal Murray.\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1369, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999196857093, \"rank\": 4.270309666053133e-08, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1404, \"end\": 1407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1639236860187865e-21, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 1424, \"end\": 1447, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shai_Gilgeous-Alexander\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shai Gilgeous-Alexander\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shai_Gilgeous-Alexander\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shai_Gilgeous-Alexander\"}, {\"begin\": 1452, \"end\": 1464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamal_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jamal Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamal_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamal_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Germany, the 2023 FIBA World Cup winners, are also among the contenders alongside host nation France, whose squad features the phenomenal Victor Wembanyama, the NBA Rookie of the Year.\", \"from\": 1467, \"to\": 1651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1467, \"end\": 14